To make a good Sacramental Confession (or Sacrament of Reconciliation), the Church recommends five essential steps (CCC 1450-1460):

1. Careful Examination of Conscience before God;
2. Sincere sorrow and contrition for sins;
3. Firm purpose of amendment (resolving to sin no more);
4. Oral confession of sins to the parish priest;
5. Completion of the penance assigned by the confessor.
